{
  "video_id": "s2cixaL9H3U",
  "title": "How to let go of being a \"good\" person â€” and become a better person | Dolly Chugh",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Krystian Aparta"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 13515.0,
      "end_time": 17221.0,
      "text": "So a friend of mine was riding in a taxi to the airport the other day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17245.0,
      "end_time": 19955.0,
      "text": "and on the way, she was chatting with the taxi driver,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 19979.0,
      "end_time": 22407.0,
      "text": "and he said to her, with total sincerity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22432.0,
      "end_time": 25718.0,
      "text": "\"I can tell you are a really good person.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25742.0,
      "end_time": 27559.0,
      "text": "And when she told me this story later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 27583.0,
      "end_time": 30758.0,
      "text": "she said she couldn&#39;t believe how good it made her feel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 30782.0,
      "end_time": 32841.0,
      "text": "that it meant a lot to her."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 32865.0,
      "end_time": 35891.0,
      "text": "Now that may seem like a strong reaction from my friend"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 35915.0,
      "end_time": 38119.0,
      "text": "to the words of a total stranger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 38143.0,
      "end_time": 39761.0,
      "text": "but she&#39;s not alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39785.0,
      "end_time": 41150.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m a social scientist."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 41174.0,
      "end_time": 43827.0,
      "text": "I study the psychology of good people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 43851.0,
      "end_time": 48141.0,
      "text": "and research in my field says many of us care deeply"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 48165.0,
      "end_time": 53166.0,
      "text": "about feeling like a good person and being seen as a good person."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53467.0,
      "end_time": 58300.0,
      "text": "Now, your definition of \"good person\" and your definition of \"good person\""
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 58324.0,
      "end_time": 61640.0,
      "text": "and maybe the taxi driver&#39;s definition of \"good person\" --"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61880.0,
      "end_time": 63710.0,
      "text": "we may not all have the same definition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63950.0,
      "end_time": 65920.0,
      "text": "but within whatever our definition is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65944.0,
      "end_time": 68745.0,
      "text": "that moral identity is important to many of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 69154.0,
      "end_time": 74375.0,
      "text": "Now, if somebody challenges it, like they question us for a joke we tell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74399.0,
      "end_time": 77820.0,
      "text": "or maybe we say our workforce is homogenous,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 77106.0,
      "end_time": 80850.0,
      "text": "or a slippery business expense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 80109.0,
      "end_time": 83306.0,
      "text": "we go into red-zone defensiveness a lot of the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 83331.0,
      "end_time": 86422.0,
      "text": "I mean, sometimes we call out"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 86446.0,
      "end_time": 90115.0,
      "text": "all the ways in which we help people from marginalized groups,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 90139.0,
      "end_time": 91907.0,
      "text": "or we donate to charity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 91931.0,
      "end_time": 95970.0,
      "text": "or the hours we volunteer to nonprofits."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 95994.0,
      "end_time": 99685.0,
      "text": "We work to protect that good person identity."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 99709.0,
      "end_time": 101645.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s important to many of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 102517.0,
      "end_time": 104375.0,
      "text": "But what if I told you this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 104399.0,
      "end_time": 109113.0,
      "text": "What if I told you that our attachment to being good people"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 109137.0,
      "end_time": 111653.0,
      "text": "is getting in the way of us being better people?"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 112225.0,
      "end_time": 118550.0,
      "text": "What if I told you that our definition of \"good person\" is so narrow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 118575.0,
      "end_time": 121106.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s scientifically impossible to meet?"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 121806.0,
      "end_time": 125830.0,
      "text": "And what if I told you the path to being better people"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 125107.0,
      "end_time": 128430.0,
      "text": "just begins with letting go of being a good person?"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 128876.0,
      "end_time": 131516.0,
      "text": "Now, let me tell you a little bit about the research"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 131540.0,
      "end_time": 133120.0,
      "text": "about how the human mind works"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 133360.0,
      "end_time": 134186.0,
      "text": "to explain."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 134540.0,
      "end_time": 138648.0,
      "text": "The brain relies on shortcuts to do a lot of its work."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 138672.0,
      "end_time": 140297.0,
      "text": "That means a lot of the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 140321.0,
      "end_time": 143649.0,
      "text": "your mental processes are taking place outside of your awareness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 143673.0,
      "end_time": 148411.0,
      "text": "like in low-battery, low-power mode in the back of your mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 149880.0,
      "end_time": 152549.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s, in fact, the premise of bounded rationality."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 152573.0,
      "end_time": 156140.0,
      "text": "Bounded rationality is the Nobel Prize-winning idea"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 156380.0,
      "end_time": 158880.0,
      "text": "that the human mind has limited storage resources,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 158904.0,
      "end_time": 161000.0,
      "text": "limited processing power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 161240.0,
      "end_time": 165560.0,
      "text": "and as a result, it relies on shortcuts to do a lot of its work."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 165571.0,
      "end_time": 167950.0,
      "text": "So for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 167833.0,
      "end_time": 170466.0,
      "text": "some scientists estimate that in any given moment ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 171270.0,
      "end_time": 173350.0,
      "text": "Better, better click, right? There we go."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 173374.0,
      "end_time": 174381.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 174405.0,
      "end_time": 175649.0,
      "text": "At any given moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 175673.0,
      "end_time": 179477.0,
      "text": "11 million pieces of information are coming into your mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 180540.0,
      "end_time": 181670.0,
      "text": "Eleven million."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 181694.0,
      "end_time": 184566.0,
      "text": "And only 40 of them are being processed consciously."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 185510.0,
      "end_time": 187273.0,
      "text": "So 11 million, 40."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 188140.0,
      "end_time": 190230.0,
      "text": "I mean, has this ever happened to you?"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 190480.0,
      "end_time": 192402.0,
      "text": "Have you ever had a really busy day at work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 192426.0,
      "end_time": 194155.0,
      "text": "and you drive home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 194179.0,
      "end_time": 196397.0,
      "text": "and when you get in the door,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 196421.0,
      "end_time": 199668.0,
      "text": "you realize you don&#39;t even remember the drive home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 199693.0,
      "end_time": 202196.0,
      "text": "like whether you had green lights or red lights."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 202220.0,
      "end_time": 204630.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t even remember. You were on autopilot."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 204974.0,
      "end_time": 208261.0,
      "text": "Or have you ever opened the fridge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 208285.0,
      "end_time": 210357.0,
      "text": "looked for the butter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 210381.0,
      "end_time": 213325.0,
      "text": "swore there is no butter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 213349.0,
      "end_time": 216965.0,
      "text": "and then realized the butter was right in front of you the whole time?"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 216990.0,
      "end_time": 220511.0,
      "text": "These are the kinds of \"whoops\" moments that make us giggle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 220535.0,
      "end_time": 222546.0,
      "text": "and this is what happens in a brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 222570.0,
      "end_time": 226144.0,
      "text": "that can handle 11 million pieces of information coming in"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 226168.0,
      "end_time": 228745.0,
      "text": "with only 40 being processed consciously."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 228769.0,
      "end_time": 232149.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the bounded part of bounded rationality."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 235352.0,
      "end_time": 237829.0,
      "text": "This work on bounded rationality"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 237853.0,
      "end_time": 242190.0,
      "text": "is what&#39;s inspired work I&#39;ve done with my collaborators"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 242430.0,
      "end_time": 244678.0,
      "text": "Max Bazerman and Mahzarin Banaji,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 244702.0,
      "end_time": 247347.0,
      "text": "on what we call bounded ethicality."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 247702.0,
      "end_time": 250774.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s the same premise as bounded rationality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 250798.0,
      "end_time": 256399.0,
      "text": "that we have a human mind that is bounded in some sort of way"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 256423.0,
      "end_time": 258505.0,
      "text": "and relying on shortcuts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 258529.0,
      "end_time": 262354.0,
      "text": "and that those shortcuts can sometimes lead us astray."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 262886.0,
      "end_time": 264411.0,
      "text": "With bounded rationality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 264435.0,
      "end_time": 268121.0,
      "text": "perhaps it affects the cereal we buy in the grocery store,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 268145.0,
      "end_time": 271228.0,
      "text": "or the product we launch in the boardroom."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 271836.0,
      "end_time": 274519.0,
      "text": "With bounded ethicality, the human mind,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 274543.0,
      "end_time": 276622.0,
      "text": "the same human mind,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 276646.0,
      "end_time": 278138.0,
      "text": "is making decisions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 278162.0,
      "end_time": 280948.0,
      "text": "and here, it&#39;s about who to hire next,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 280972.0,
      "end_time": 282621.0,
      "text": "or what joke to tell"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 282646.0,
      "end_time": 284868.0,
      "text": "or that slippery business decision."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 286157.0,
      "end_time": 290760.0,
      "text": "So let me give you an example of bounded ethicality at work."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 290784.0,
      "end_time": 293570.0,
      "text": "Unconscious bias is one place"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 293594.0,
      "end_time": 297103.0,
      "text": "where we see the effects of bounded ethicality."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 297127.0,
      "end_time": 301513.0,
      "text": "So unconscious bias refers to associations we have in our mind,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 301537.0,
      "end_time": 305827.0,
      "text": "the shortcuts your brain is using to organize information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 305851.0,
      "end_time": 308115.0,
      "text": "very likely outside of your awareness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 308139.0,
      "end_time": 311591.0,
      "text": "not necessarily lining up with your conscious beliefs."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 312503.0,
      "end_time": 315270.0,
      "text": "Researchers Nosek, Banaji and Greenwald"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 315510.0,
      "end_time": 317782.0,
      "text": "have looked at data from millions of people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 317806.0,
      "end_time": 320563.0,
      "text": "and what they&#39;ve found is, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 320587.0,
      "end_time": 324800.0,
      "text": "most white Americans can more quickly and easily"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 324104.0,
      "end_time": 328373.0,
      "text": "associate white people and good things"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 328397.0,
      "end_time": 330690.0,
      "text": "than black people and good things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 331650.0,
      "end_time": 337263.0,
      "text": "and most men and women can more quickly and easily associate"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 337288.0,
      "end_time": 341590.0,
      "text": "men and science than women and science."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 342137.0,
      "end_time": 346424.0,
      "text": "And these associations don&#39;t necessarily line up"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 346448.0,
      "end_time": 348323.0,
      "text": "with what people consciously think."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 348347.0,
      "end_time": 351680.0,
      "text": "They may have very egalitarian views, in fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 352206.0,
      "end_time": 356619.0,
      "text": "So sometimes, that 11 million and that 40 just don&#39;t line up."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 357402.0,
      "end_time": 359369.0,
      "text": "And here&#39;s another example:"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 359393.0,
      "end_time": 360885.0,
      "text": "conflicts of interest."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 361372.0,
      "end_time": 365182.0,
      "text": "So we tend to underestimate how much a small gift --"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 365206.0,
      "end_time": 368849.0,
      "text": "imagine a ballpoint pen or dinner --"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 368873.0,
      "end_time": 373310.0,
      "text": "how much that small gift can affect our decision making."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 373852.0,
      "end_time": 378178.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t realize that our mind is unconsciously lining up evidence"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 378202.0,
      "end_time": 381733.0,
      "text": "to support the point of view of the gift-giver,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 381757.0,
      "end_time": 386578.0,
      "text": "no matter how hard we&#39;re consciously trying to be objective and professional."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 387689.0,
      "end_time": 389408.0,
      "text": "We also see bounded ethicality --"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 389432.0,
      "end_time": 392809.0,
      "text": "despite our attachment to being good people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 392833.0,
      "end_time": 394914.0,
      "text": "we still make mistakes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 394938.0,
      "end_time": 398949.0,
      "text": "and we make mistakes that sometimes hurt other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 398973.0,
      "end_time": 401443.0,
      "text": "that sometimes promote injustice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 401467.0,
      "end_time": 403491.0,
      "text": "despite our best attempts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 403516.0,
      "end_time": 407633.0,
      "text": "and we explain away our mistakes rather than learning from them."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 408810.0,
      "end_time": 411263.0,
      "text": "Like, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 411287.0,
      "end_time": 415870.0,
      "text": "when I got an email from a female student in my class"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 415112.0,
      "end_time": 417660.0,
      "text": "saying that a reading I had assigned,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 417684.0,
      "end_time": 420438.0,
      "text": "a reading I had been assigning for years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 420462.0,
      "end_time": 421893.0,
      "text": "was sexist."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 422738.0,
      "end_time": 428326.0,
      "text": "Or when I confused two students in my class"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 428350.0,
      "end_time": 429707.0,
      "text": "of the same race --"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 429731.0,
      "end_time": 432100.0,
      "text": "look nothing alike --"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 432250.0,
      "end_time": 434183.0,
      "text": "when I confused them for each other"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 434208.0,
      "end_time": 436873.0,
      "text": "more than once, in front of everybody."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 437885.0,
      "end_time": 442207.0,
      "text": "These kinds of mistakes send us, send me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 442232.0,
      "end_time": 445670.0,
      "text": "into red-zone defensiveness."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 445910.0,
      "end_time": 449321.0,
      "text": "They leave us fighting for that good person identity."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 450189.0,
      "end_time": 454529.0,
      "text": "But the latest work that I&#39;ve been doing on bounded ethicality with Mary Kern"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 454553.0,
      "end_time": 458125.0,
      "text": "says that we&#39;re not only prone to mistakes --"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 458149.0,
      "end_time": 463388.0,
      "text": "that tendency towards mistakes depends on how close we are to that red zone."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 463412.0,
      "end_time": 467611.0,
      "text": "So most of the time, nobody&#39;s challenging our good person identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 467635.0,
      "end_time": 469794.0,
      "text": "and so we&#39;re not thinking too much"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 469818.0,
      "end_time": 472151.0,
      "text": "about the ethical implications of our decisions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 472175.0,
      "end_time": 476540.0,
      "text": "and our model shows that we&#39;re then spiraling"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 476780.0,
      "end_time": 480816.0,
      "text": "towards less and less ethical behavior most of the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 480841.0,
      "end_time": 483689.0,
      "text": "On the other hand, somebody might challenge our identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 483713.0,
      "end_time": 487212.0,
      "text": "or, upon reflection, we may be challenging it ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 487236.0,
      "end_time": 491360.0,
      "text": "So the ethical implications of our decisions become really salient,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 491384.0,
      "end_time": 497121.0,
      "text": "and in those cases, we spiral towards more and more good person behavior,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 497145.0,
      "end_time": 498986.0,
      "text": "or, to be more precise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 499100.0,
      "end_time": 503548.0,
      "text": "towards more and more behavior that makes us feel like a good person,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 503572.0,
      "end_time": 506160.0,
      "text": "which isn&#39;t always the same, of course."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 507413.0,
      "end_time": 511560.0,
      "text": "The idea with bounded ethicality"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 511800.0,
      "end_time": 515282.0,
      "text": "is that we are perhaps overestimating"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 515306.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520474.00000000006,
      "text": "the importance our inner compass is playing in our ethical decisions."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 520498.00000000006,
      "end_time": 524983.0,
      "text": "We perhaps are overestimating how much our self-interest"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 525700.0,
      "end_time": 528378.0,
      "text": "is driving our decisions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 528403.0,
      "end_time": 534118.0,
      "text": "and perhaps we don&#39;t realize how much our self-view as a good person"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 534142.0,
      "end_time": 536666.0,
      "text": "is affecting our behavior,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 536690.0,
      "end_time": 542175.0,
      "text": "that in fact, we&#39;re working so hard to protect that good person identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 542199.0,
      "end_time": 544492.0,
      "text": "to keep out of that red zone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 544517.0,
      "end_time": 549871.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;re not actually giving ourselves space to learn from our mistakes"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 549895.0,
      "end_time": 552212.0,
      "text": "and actually be better people."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 553998.0,
      "end_time": 557390.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s perhaps because we expect it to be easy."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 557630.0,
      "end_time": 561153.0,
      "text": "We have this definition of good person that&#39;s either-or."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 561177.0,
      "end_time": 564216.0,
      "text": "Either you are a good person or you&#39;re not."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 564240.0,
      "end_time": 566860.0,
      "text": "Either you have integrity or you don&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 566884.0,
      "end_time": 571516.0,
      "text": "Either you are a racist or a sexist or a homophobe or you&#39;re not."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 571540.0,
      "end_time": 575522.0,
      "text": "And in this either-or definition, there&#39;s no room to grow."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 576444.0,
      "end_time": 577594.0,
      "text": "And by the way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 577619.0,
      "end_time": 580603.0,
      "text": "this is not what we do in most parts of our lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 580627.0,
      "end_time": 583102.0,
      "text": "Life, if you needed to learn accounting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 583126.0,
      "end_time": 584819.0,
      "text": "you would take an accounting class,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 584843.0,
      "end_time": 587137.0,
      "text": "or if you become a parent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 587161.0,
      "end_time": 590667.0,
      "text": "we pick up a book and we read about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 590692.0,
      "end_time": 593319.0,
      "text": "We talk to experts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 593343.0,
      "end_time": 594796.0,
      "text": "we learn from our mistakes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 594821.0,
      "end_time": 596320.0,
      "text": "we update our knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 596344.0,
      "end_time": 598310.0,
      "text": "we just keep getting better."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 598835.0,
      "end_time": 600791.0,
      "text": "But when it comes to being a good person,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 600815.0,
      "end_time": 603307.0,
      "text": "we think it&#39;s something we&#39;re just supposed to know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 603331.0,
      "end_time": 604594.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re just supposed to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 604618.0,
      "end_time": 607926.0,
      "text": "without the benefit of effort or growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 607950.0,
      "end_time": 609790.0,
      "text": "So what I&#39;ve been thinking about"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 609814.0,
      "end_time": 613966.0,
      "text": "is what if we were to just forget about being good people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 613990.0,
      "end_time": 615755.0,
      "text": "just let it go,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 615779.0,
      "end_time": 618875.0,
      "text": "and instead, set a higher standard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 618899.0,
      "end_time": 621961.0,
      "text": "a higher standard of being a good-ish person?"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 624891.0,
      "end_time": 629113.0,
      "text": "A good-ish person absolutely still makes mistakes."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 629138.0,
      "end_time": 632180.0,
      "text": "As a good-ish person, I&#39;m making them all the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 632881.0,
      "end_time": 637255.0,
      "text": "But as a good-ish person, I&#39;m trying to learn from them, own them."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 637279.0,
      "end_time": 640838.0,
      "text": "I expect them and I go after them."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 640862.0,
      "end_time": 643466.0,
      "text": "I understand there are costs to these mistakes."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 643490.0,
      "end_time": 647558.0,
      "text": "When it comes to issues like ethics and bias and diversity and inclusion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 647582.0,
      "end_time": 650724.0,
      "text": "there are real costs to real people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 650748.0,
      "end_time": 652630.0,
      "text": "and I accept that."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 654602.0,
      "end_time": 656483.0,
      "text": "As a good-ish person, in fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 656507.0,
      "end_time": 659189.0,
      "text": "I become better at noticing my own mistakes."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 659214.0,
      "end_time": 661514.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t wait for people to point them out."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 661538.0,
      "end_time": 663680.0,
      "text": "I practice finding them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 663704.0,
      "end_time": 664979.0,
      "text": "and as a result ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 665911.0,
      "end_time": 669527.0,
      "text": "Sure, sometimes it can be embarrassing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 669552.0,
      "end_time": 671414.0,
      "text": "it can be uncomfortable."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 671438.0,
      "end_time": 674784.0,
      "text": "We put ourselves in a vulnerable place, sometimes."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 675968.0,
      "end_time": 678118.0,
      "text": "But through all that vulnerability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 678143.0,
      "end_time": 682483.0,
      "text": "just like in everything else we&#39;ve tried to ever get better at,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 682507.0,
      "end_time": 683809.0,
      "text": "we see progress."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 683833.0,
      "end_time": 684983.0,
      "text": "We see growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 685800.0,
      "end_time": 687937.0,
      "text": "We allow ourselves to get better."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 689160.0,
      "end_time": 692437.0,
      "text": "Why wouldn&#39;t we give ourselves that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 692944.0,
      "end_time": 697471.0,
      "text": "In every other part of our lives, we give ourselves room to grow --"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 697495.0,
      "end_time": 700260.0,
      "text": "except in this one, where it matters most."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 701256.0,
      "end_time": 702406.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 702431.0,
      "end_time": 707310.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}